ColladaLoader

public ColladaLoader(java.lang.String filename,
                     processing.core.PApplet applet)
this is the entry constructor to load a sketchup or serialized file. there exist reserved suffixes: - '.dae' or '.kmz' are sketchup files - '.dat' is a raw serialized ColladaLoader model (see method save())

Parameters:
the - Filename (either 'foo.dae', 'foo.kmz' or 'foo.dat')
the - main applet of processing (never null)
Method Detail

draw

public void draw()

A comfortable method to draw the complete dae/kmz to current scetch. It's allowed to implement a custom code from the following template:

 public void drawModel()
    {
        //reset shapes
        noStroke(); //reset if last draw was lines
        fill(127); //define a standart color
        
        
       for (Triangle tri : model.getTriangles())
       {

          if (!tri.containsTexture)
          {
              fill(tri.colour.red*255, tri.colour.green*255, tri.colour.blue*255, tri.colour.transparency * 255);
              beginShape(TRIANGLE);

              vertex(tri.A.x, tri.A.y, tri.A.z);
              vertex(tri.B.x, tri.B.y, tri.B.z);
              vertex(tri.C.x, tri.C.y, tri.C.z);

              endShape();

          } else
          {
              beginShape(TRIANGLE);
              texture(tri.imageReference);
                
              vertex(tri.A.x, tri.A.y, tri.A.z, tri.texA.x, tri.texA.y);
              vertex(tri.B.x, tri.B.y, tri.B.z, tri.texB.x, tri.texB.y);
              vertex(tri.C.x, tri.C.y, tri.C.z, tri.texC.x, tri.texC.y);

              endShape();

          }

       }

       for (Line lin : model.getLines())
       {
                strokeWeight(1);//define thickness of drawn lines
           stroke(lin.colour.red*255, lin.colour.green*255, lin.colour.blue*255);
           line(lin.A.x, lin.A.y, lin.A.z, lin.B.x, lin.B.y, lin.B.z);

       }
    }
